><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Brice to be jailed and perhaps scourged.</span><hr size=1>       Freeport, Norrath--Brice Lee, a 27-year-old Monk and longtime employee at Jade Tiger Den, stealthily took the lives of 12 co-workers Monday after suffering what investigators theorize was &quot;a breakdown due to guild growth-related stress.&quot; <br>
<br>
    The disgruntled monk was later captured by guards while attempting to flee on foot across roof-tops after a levitation spell wore off prematurely. <br>
<br>
      Brice, who, according to Den owner and gnome pimp Gomersaul, had been &quot;unusually quiet lately, even for him,&quot; was reportedly deeply upset about his lack of a rakusha cloak. <br>
<br>
      Following a 9 a.m. staff meeting in which management discussed the possibility of demoting Brice to a position as Special Secretary and Gofur For Folks Dat Needz Phat L00tz nd Other Chit, the Monk rose, gave a shallow bow and returned to his shadowy corner behind the bar. <br>
<br>
      Nysa said that shortly thereafter, she and other employees could hear what sounded like a Quellious death-consecration ceremony, as well as &quot;sharpening sounds,&quot; coming from Brices's corner. <br>
<br>
      The first deaths are believed to have occurred just minutes later. <br>
<br>
      &quot;After the meeting, I was having lunch in the company cafeteria with Montyy, Adus and Brekthar,&quot; bar-slut Sweetiepie Beggarslayer said. &quot;I looked down for a moment to take a bite of my sandwich, and when I looked up, Montyy's head had been cut off and placed on his tray, Adus had been sliced in half so neatly that his hair was still in place, and there was blood dripping from the ceiling directly above Brekthars' chair.&quot; Brekthar's dismembered body was later found inside the ceiling. <br>
<br>
      Sales supervisor Syllie, whose workspace was directly across from Brices's and who on several occasions had questioned the wisdom of having a bar monk, was the next victim, killed instantly when a single thrust from a razor-sharp ninjato-katana sword pierced through the wall, sheared through a keg of ale, and plunged through her heart. <br>
<br>
      Brice then snapped the neck of associate marketing coordinator Reyu, shredded the body of brewing manager Sicko with 18 shurukin, and used his 100 hands technique to stop the heart of brothel intern Mydnight long enough to drive the intern's nose through her brain with a single punch. <br>
<br>
      After killing Mydnight, Brice ran along the top of the ceiling to reach the office of senior L00tz supervisor Robion, who was hit with eight arrows from Brice's saisumimen, a whisper-quiet recurved bow of ancient design and unparalleled craftsmanship. <br>
<br>
      &quot;Brices's first arrow severed Robion's vocal cords, silencing him without hitting any of the major arteries or veins in the neck and without penetrating deeply enough to touch the spinal column,&quot; Freeport Malitia's ballistics expert Brunosi Swifthammer said. &quot;An arrow was then fired into each of the seven henzoitoichi, or major nerve clusters, of Robion's body. Though the hits themselves were not fatal, the excruciating pain killed Robion within 10 seconds.&quot; <br>
<br>
       Four more Jade Tiger employees were later found dead, two of them eviscerated, one garrotted and one impaled upon cunningly folded Sali's Writ page. Forensics experts said none of the bodies seemed to indicate that the victims were aware of the monk's presence at the moment of death.  Pogue, upon seeing the ghastly scene, immediately took his own life with a mod-rod.<br>
<br>
      Brice was relatively new to Freeport, having been transferred from the Godless Monk Clan's mountain headquarters in Qeynos in December 1998. Following the brutal slaying of his Grandmaster at the hands of a rival school, Brice requested permission to perform the Ritual of Blood Revenge, but was sold to Gomersaul instead. <br>
<br>
      Co-workers said that despite Brice's quiet demeanor, he would occasionally voice dissatisfaction with his work environment. <br>
<br>
      &quot;He didn't say much. Half the time, I didn't even know he was around,&quot; payroll secretary Thoras said. &quot;But when he did talk, it was usually to complain about how hard it was to get a decent cup of Blackburrow stout around Freeport, or how he shouldn't have to listen to Astrix because he wasn't a daimyo warlord.  But I honestly didn't think it would come to this. I mean, he was basically a shy guy.&quot; <br>
<br>
      Brice has issued a statement through his lawyer asking that he be allowed to perform ritual seppuku suicide in his cell. He also requested that Quichane, master of Myojinsoga-style swordsmanship and CEO of the Jade Tiger Den, be his second in the ceremony.<br>
